on neural plasticity; and the dawn of artificial intelligence, with its potential to simulate, replicate, and ultimately surpass the workings of the brain. Malabou concludes that a dialogue between human and cybernetic intelligence offers the best if not the only means to build a democratic future. A strikingly original exploration of our changing notions of intelligence and the human and their far-reaching philosophical and political implications, Morphing Intelligence is an essential analysis of the porous border between symbolic and biological life at a time when once-clear distinctions between mind and machine have become uncertain.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 21. Jun 2021) 0aArtificial intelligence. 0aHuman Brain Project. 0aIntellect. 0aNeuroinformatics. 0aNeurosciences. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Mind & Body.2bisacsh1 aShread, Carolyn.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertColumbia University Press Complete eBook-Package 2019z978311065195908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019 Englishz978311061076508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019z9783110664232oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Philosophy 2019 Englishz978311061055008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Philosophy 2019z9783110606423oZDB-23-DPH40uhttps://doi.org/10.7312/mala1873640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780231547239423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780231547239.jpg  a978-3-11-061055-0  EBOOK PACKAGE Philosophy 2019 Englishb2019  a978-3-11-061076-5  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019 Englishb2019  a978-3-11-065195-9  Columbia University Press Complete eBook-Package 2019b2019  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEB